    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Starting at 7th level, if you spend at least 1 minute observing or interacting with another creature outside combat, you can learn certain information about its capabilities compared to your own. The DM tells you information based on the two of the following characteristics of your choice:</p><ul><li>Strength score (equal, superior or inferior to you and if proficient in the saving throw)</li><li>Dexterity score (equal, superior or inferior to you and if proficient in the saving throw)</li><li>Constitution score (equal, superior or inferior to you and if proficient in the saving throw)</li><li>Armor Class</li><li>Current hit points</li><li>Total class levels (if any and if any levels are in fighter)</li></ul>",
